33 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38 #ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40 #elif USING_V8_SHARED
41 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42 #else
43 # define V8_EXPORT
44 #endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45 
46 #else // V8_OS_WIN
47 
48 // Setup for Linux shared library export.
49 #if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50 # ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51 # define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52 # else
53 # define V8_EXPORT
54 # endif
55 #else
56 # define V8_EXPORT
57 #endif
58 
59 #endif // V8_OS_WIN

165 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
166  while (false) { \
167  *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
168  }

201 template <class T>
202 class Local {
203  public:
204  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
205  template <class S>
206  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
207  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
213  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
214  }
215 
219  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
220 
224  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
225 
226  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
227 
228  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
229 
236  template <class S>
237  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
238  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
239  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
240  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
241  if (b == 0) return false;
242  return *a == *b;
243  }
244 
245  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
246  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
247  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
248  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
249  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
250  if (b == 0) return false;
251  return *a == *b;
252  }
253 
260  template <class S>
261  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
262  return !operator==(that);
263  }
264 
265  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
266  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
267  return !operator==(that);
268  }

275  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
276 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
277  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
278  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
279  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
280 #endif
281  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
282  }
283 
289  template <class S>
290  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
291  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
292  }
293 
299  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
300  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
301  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
302 
303  private:
304  friend class Utils;
305  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
306  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
307  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
308  template<class F> friend class Local;
309  template <class F>
310  friend class MaybeLocal;
311  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
312  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
313  friend class String;
314  friend class Object;
315  friend class Context;
316  friend class Isolate;

326  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
327  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
328  template <class F>
329  friend class ReturnValue;

416 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
417 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
418 
419 template <typename T>
420 class WeakCallbackInfo {
421  public:
422  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
423 
424  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
425  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
426  Callback* callback)
427  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
428  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
429  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
430  }
431  }
432 
433  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
434  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
435  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
436 
437  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
438  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
439  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
440  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
441  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
442  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
443  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
444 
445  private:
446  Isolate* isolate_;
447  T* parameter_;
448  Callback* callback_;
449  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
450 };
451 
452 
453 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
454 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
455 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
456 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
457 // possible to request a second pass callback.
458 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
459

634 template<class T>
635 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
636  public:
637  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
638  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
639  template<class S, class M>
640  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
641  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
642  Uncompilable<Object>();
643  }
644  // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
645  template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
646  TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
647  }
648 };

659  template<class S, class M>

661  CopyablePersistent* dest) {

675 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
676  public:
680  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
686  template <class S>
687  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
688  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
689  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
690  }
696  template <class S, class M2>
697  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
698  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
699  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
700  }
707  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
708  Copy(that);
709  }
710  template <class S, class M2>
711  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
712  Copy(that);
713  }
714  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
715  Copy(that);
716  return *this;
717  }
718  template <class S, class M2>
719  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
720  Copy(that);
721  return *this;
722  }
728  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
729  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
730  }
731 
732  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
733  template <class S>
734  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
735 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
736  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
737  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
738  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
739 #endif
740  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
741  }
742 
743  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
744  template <class S>
745  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
746  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
747  }
748 
749  private:
750  friend class Isolate;
751  friend class Utils;
752  template<class F> friend class Local;
753  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
754  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
755 
756  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
757  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
758  template<class S, class M2>
759  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
760 };

768 template <class T>
769 class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
770  public:
774  V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
780  template <class S>
781  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
782  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
783  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
784  }
790  template <class S>
791  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
792  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
793  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
794  }
798  V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
799  other.val_ = nullptr;
800  }
801  V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
805  template <class S>
806  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
807  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
808  if (this != &rhs) {
809  this->Reset();
810  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
811  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
812  }
813  return *this;
814  }
818  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
819 
820  /*
821  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
822  */
823  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
824 
825  Global(const Global&) = delete;
826  void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
827 
828  private:
829  template <class F>
830  friend class ReturnValue;
831  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
832 };

854 class V8_EXPORT HandleScope {

877  static internal::Object** CreateHandle(internal::Isolate* isolate,
878  internal::Object* value);
879 
880  private:
881  // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
882  // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
883  void* operator new(size_t size);

900  // a HeapObject* in their shortcuts.

1019 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1020  public:
1021  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1022  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1023  bool is_module = false)
1024  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1025  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1026  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1027  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1028  : flags_(flags &
1029  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1030 
1031  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1032  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1033  }
1034  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1035  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1036  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1037 
1038  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1039 
1040  private:
1041  enum {
1042  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1043  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1044  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1045  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1046  };
1047  const int flags_;
1048 };

1252 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1253  public:
1261  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1262  enum BufferPolicy {
1263  BufferNotOwned,
1264  BufferOwned
1265  };
1266 
1267  CachedData()
1268  : data(NULL),
1269  length(0),
1270  rejected(false),
1271  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1272 
1273  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1274  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1275  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1276  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1277  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1278  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1279  ~CachedData();
1280  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1281  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1282  const uint8_t* data;
1283  int length;
1284  bool rejected;
1285  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1286 
1287  // Prevent copying.
1288  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1289  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1290  };
1291 
1295  class Source {
1296  public:
1297  // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1298  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1299  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1300  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1301  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1302  V8_INLINE ~Source();
1303 
1304  // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1305  // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1306  // alive.
1307  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1308 
1309  V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1310 
1311  // Prevent copying.
1312  Source(const Source&) = delete;
1313  Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1314 
1315  private:
1316  friend class ScriptCompiler;
1317 
1318  Local<String> source_string;
1319 
1320  // Origin information
1321  Local<Value> resource_name;
1322  Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1323  Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1324  ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1325  Local<Value> source_map_url;
1326  Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1327 
1328  // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1329  // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1330  // set when calling a compile method.
1331  CachedData* cached_data;
1332  };

3082  //
3083  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value

3105  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3106  //
3107  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3108  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3109  //
3110  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3111  //
3112  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3113  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3114  //
3115  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.

3117  // Returns true on success.

3548 template<typename T>
3549 class ReturnValue {
3550  public:
3551  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3552  : value_(that.value_) {
3553  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3554  }
3555  // Local setters
3556  template <typename S>
3557  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3558  void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3559  template <typename S>
3560  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3561  template <typename S>
3562  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3563  // Fast primitive setters
3564  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3565  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3566  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3567  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3568  // Fast JS primitive setters
3569  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3570  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3571  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3572  // Convenience getter for Isolate
3573  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3574 
3575  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3576  template <typename S>
3577  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3578 
3579  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3580  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3581  // value.
3582  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3583 
3584  private:
3585  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3586  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3587  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3588  template <class F, class G, class H>
3589  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3590  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3591  V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3592  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3593  internal::Object** value_;
3594 };

4044 // TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4045 // consistency with internal APIs.
4046 class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4047  public:
4048  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4049  // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4050  typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4051 
4052  // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4053  // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4054  class TransferrableModule final {
4055  public:
4056  TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4057  TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4058 
4059  TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4060  TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4061 
4062  private:
4063  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4064  friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4065  TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4066  : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4067 
4068  OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4069  OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4070  };
4071 
4072  // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4073  // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4074  // of this wasm compiled module.
4075  TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4076 
4077  // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4078  // a TransferrableModule.
4079  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4080  Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4081 
4082  // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4083  Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4084 
4085  // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4086  // uncompiled bytes.
4087  SerializedModule Serialize();
4088 
4089  // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4090  // uncompiled bytes.
4091  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4092  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4093  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4094  V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4095 
4096  private:
4097  // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4098  // implemented
4099  friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4100 
4101  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4102  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4103  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4104  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4105  const uint8_t* start,
4106  size_t length);
4107  static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4108  const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4109  return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4110  }
4111 
4112  WasmCompiledModule();
4113  static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4114 };

6045  return max_semi_space_size_in_kb_;

6055  max_old_space_size_ = limit_in_mb;
6056  }
6057  V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("max_executable_size_ is subsumed by max_old_space_size_",

6060  }
6061  V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("max_executable_size_ is subsumed by max_old_space_size_",

6063  max_executable_size_ = limit_in_mb;

6071  }

6074  max_zone_pool_size_ = bytes;
6075  }
6076

6080

6082  int max_old_space_size_;
6083  int max_executable_size_;

6497 struct JitCodeEvent {
6498  enum EventType {
6499  CODE_ADDED,
6500  CODE_MOVED,
6501  CODE_REMOVED,
6502  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6503  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6504  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6505  };
6506  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6507  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6508  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6509  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6510  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6511  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6512 
6513  // Type of event.
6514  EventType type;
6515  // Start of the instructions.
6516  void* code_start;
6517  // Size of the instructions.
6518  size_t code_len;
6519  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6520  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6521  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6522  // code line information which is returned from the
6523  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6524  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6525  void* user_data;
6526 
6527  struct name_t {
6528  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6529  // zero-terminated.
6530  const char* str;
6531  // Number of chars in str.
6532  size_t len;
6533  };
6534 
6535  struct line_info_t {
6536  // PC offset
6537  size_t offset;
6538  // Code position
6539  size_t pos;
6540  // The position type.
6541  PositionType position_type;
6542  };
6543 
6544  union {
6545  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6546  struct name_t name;
6547 
6548  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6549  struct line_info_t line_info;
6550 
6551  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6552  void* new_code_start;
6553  };
6554 };
6555 
6561 enum RAILMode {
6562  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6563  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6564  // Throughput may be throttled.
6565  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6566  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6567  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6568  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6569  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6570  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6571  // in this mode.
6572  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6573  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6574  // turn off latency optimizations.
6575  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6576 };
6577

8099 template <class T>
8100 class Maybe {
8101  public:
8102  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8103  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8104 
8108  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8109 
8114  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8115  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8116  return IsJust();
8117  }
8118 
8123  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8124  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8125  return value_;
8126  }
8127 
8132  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8133  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8134  }
8135 
8136  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8137  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8138  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8139  }
8140 
8141  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8142  return !operator==(other);
8143  }
8144 
8145  private:
8146  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8147  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8148 
8149  bool has_value_;
8150  T value_;
8151 
8152  template <class U>
8153  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8154  template <class U>
8155  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8156 };
8157 
8158 template <class T>
8159 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8160  return Maybe<T>();
8161 }
8162 
8163 template <class T>
8164 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8165  return Maybe<T>(t);
8166 }
8167 
8168 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
8169 template <>
8170 class Maybe<void> {
8171  public:
8172  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
8173  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
8174 
8175  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8176  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
8177  }
8178 
8179  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8180  return !operator==(other);
8181  }
8182 
8183  private:
8184  struct JustTag {};
8185 
8186  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
8187  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
8188 
8189  bool is_valid_;
8190 
8191  template <class U>
8192  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8193  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
8194 };
8195 
8196 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

8756 namespace internal {
8757 
8758 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8759 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8760 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8761 
8762 // Tag information for HeapObject.
8763 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8764 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8765 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8766 
8767 // Tag information for Smi.
8768 const int kSmiTag = 0;
8769 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8770 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8771 
8772 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8773 
8774 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8775 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8776  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8777  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8778  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8779  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8780 }
8781 
8782 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8783 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8784  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8785  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8786  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8787  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8788  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8789  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8790  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8791  }
8792  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8793  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8794  }
8795  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8796  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8797  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8798  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8799  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8800  //
8801  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8802  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8803  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8804  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8805  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8806  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8807  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8808  }
8809 };
8810 
8811 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8812 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8813  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8814  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8815  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8816  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8817  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8818  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8819  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8820  }
8821  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8822  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8823  }
8824  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8825  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8826  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8827  }
8828 };
8829 
8830 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8831 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8832 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8833 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8834 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

8857  static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
8858  static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;
8859

8861  static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
8862  static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
8863  kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
8864  static const int kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset =
8865  kExternalMemoryLimitOffset + kApiInt64Size;
8866  static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
8867  kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
8868  kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;

8870  static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
8871  static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;

8873  static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;

8875

8877  static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
8878  static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
8879  static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
8880  static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
8881  static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
8882  static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;

8885  static const int kOddballType = 0x83;

8887  static const int kJSSpecialApiObjectType = 0x410;
8888  static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0x420;

8892  static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;

8903  V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {

8905  kHeapObjectTag);

8923  return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeOffset);

8931  V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
8932  int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
8933  return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
8934  }

8936  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
8937  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8938  return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8939  }
8940 
8941  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
8942  bool value, int shift) {
8943  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8944  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8945  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
8946  }
8947 
8948  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
8949  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8950  return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
8951  }
8952 
8953  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
8954  uint8_t value) {
8955  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8956  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
8957  }
8958 
8959  V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8960  uint32_t slot,
8961  void* data) {
8962  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8963  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8964  *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
8965  }
8966 
8967  V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
8968  uint32_t slot) {
8969  const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8970  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8971  return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
8972  }
8973 
8974  V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8975  int index) {
8976  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
8977  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
8978  }
8979 
8980  template <typename T>
8981  V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
8982  const uint8_t* addr =
8983  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
8984  return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
8985  }
8986 
8987  template <typename T>
8988  V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
8989  typedef internal::Object O;
8990  typedef internal::Internals I;
8991  O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
8992  int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
8993  (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
8994  O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
8995  int value_offset =
8996  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8997  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
8998  }
8999 };

9001 // Only perform cast check for types derived from v8::Data since
9002 // other types do not implement the Cast method.
9003 template <bool PerformCheck>
9004 struct CastCheck {

9006  static void Perform(T* data);
9007 };
9008 
9009 template <>
9010 template <class T>
9011 void CastCheck<true>::Perform(T* data) {
9012  T::Cast(data);
9013 }
9014 
9015 template <>
9016 template <class T>
9017 void CastCheck<false>::Perform(T* data) {}
9018 
9019 template <class T>
9020 V8_INLINE void PerformCastCheck(T* data) {
9021  CastCheck<std::is_base_of<Data, T>::value>::Perform(data);
9022 }

9095  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9096  this->Reset();
9097  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
9098  internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
9099  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9100  M::Copy(that, this);
9101 }

9108 template <class T>
9109 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9110  typedef internal::Internals I;
9111  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9112  uint8_t node_state =
9113  I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9114  return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9115  node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9116 }

9124  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9125 }

9261 template<typename T>
9262 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9263  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9264  typedef internal::Internals I;
9265  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9266  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9267  return;

9272 template<typename T>
9273 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9274  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9275  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9276  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9277  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9278  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9279  return;
9280  }
9281  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9282 }

9284 template<typename T>
9285 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9286  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9287  typedef internal::Internals I;
9288  int root_index;
9289  if (value) {
9290  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9291  } else {
9292  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9293  }
9294  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9295 }

9297 template<typename T>
9298 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {

9302 }

9318 template <typename T>
9319 Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
9320  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9321  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
9322 }
9323 
9324 template <typename T>
9325 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9326  typedef internal::Internals I;
9327  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9328  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9329  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9330 }

9335  // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
9336  TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
9337 }

9339 template<typename T>
9340 internal::Object* ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
9341  // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
9342  return value_[-1];
9343 }

9351 template<typename T>
9352 Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
9353  if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9354  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
9355 }

9514 
9515 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9516 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9517  typedef internal::Object O;
9518  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9519  typedef internal::Internals I;
9520  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9521  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9522  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9523  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9524  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9525  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9526  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
9527  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9528  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9529  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9530  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9531  }
9532 #endif
9533  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9534 }
9535 
9536 
9537 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9538 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9539  typedef internal::Object O;
9540  typedef internal::Internals I;
9541  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9542  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9543  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9544  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9545  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9546  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9547  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
9548  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9549  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9550  }
9551 #endif
9552  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9553 }

9563 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
9564  typedef internal::Object* S;
9565  typedef internal::Internals I;
9566  I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
9567  S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
9568  return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
9569 }

9571 
9572 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9573  typedef internal::Object O;
9574  typedef internal::Internals I;
9575  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9576  String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9577  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9578  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9579  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9580  } else {
9581  result = NULL;
9582  }
9583 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9584  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9585 #endif
9586  return result;
9587 }
9588 
9589 
9590 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9591  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9592  typedef internal::Object O;
9593  typedef internal::Internals I;
9594  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9595  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9596  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9597  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9598  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9599  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9600  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9601  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9602  }
9603 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9604  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9605 #endif
9606  return resource;
9607 }

9618 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
9619  typedef internal::Object O;
9620  typedef internal::Internals I;
9621  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9622  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9623  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9624  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9625 }

9636 bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
9637  typedef internal::Object O;

9639  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9640  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9641  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9642  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
9643 }

9645 bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
9646 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9647  return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
9648 #else
9649  return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
9650 #endif
9651 }
9652 
9653 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9654  typedef internal::Object O;
9655  typedef internal::Internals I;
9656  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9657  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9658  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9659  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
9660  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
9661 }

10106 
10107 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10108  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10109  typedef internal::Internals I;
10110  const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10111  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10112  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10113  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10114  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10115  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10116  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10117  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10118  const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10119 
10120  *external_memory = amount;
10121 
10122  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10123  *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10124  allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10125  ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10126  : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10127  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10128  CheckMemoryPressure();
10129  }
10130 
10131  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10132  *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10133  }
10134 
10135  if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10136  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10137  }
10138  return *external_memory;
10139 }

10141 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10142 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10143  typedef internal::Object O;
10144  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
10145  typedef internal::Internals I;
10146  HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
10147  O** result =
10148  HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10149  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10150 #else
10151  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10152 #endif
10153 }
10154

10160 #else
10161  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
10162 #endif
10163 }
